HEADWORD: Miargyrite
<hw>Mi*ar"gy*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ less +
<?/ silver. So called because it contains less silver than some kindred
ore.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of an iron-black color, and
very sectile, consisting principally of sulphur, antimony, and
silver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mias</ent>⟦br⟧
